69-9577-fe7b5a242d7d","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Design challenge resolved (handoff session c18e-6b87-cde8-4148): the outbound differ compared in vendor shape, so its comparison helpers had no ADR 0035 §(d)-legal home (port extension was BLOCKED by plan review on 97f2/change 920; keeping them in core kept the core vendor-shaped). Resolution: the canonical-comparison principle — core compares only canonical shapes; the outbound differ canonicalizes the fetched snapshot via InboundMapper.map_remote_to_local (parity with inbound_differ.py:159) and builds vendor payloads only via the injected OutboundMapper at emission. Remediation decomposed into 5 open children: 97f2 re-scoped to the scalar port surface (project/query_project/assert_env_ready/neutral assignee error); 625b canonical field diff (+ADR §(d) amendment); eefd canonical link diff; aff0 SupportsAbsenceProbe (inbound_probe REST mechanics -> adapters/jira/probe.py, a residual missed by the original AC3 inventory); 21ca rich-text/comment-limit lazy-key literals behind FieldSanitizer/InboundMapper. Follow-up 556a (relocate inbound_fields.py) filed discovered_from, out of epic scope. Gerrit change 920 to be abandoned; its scalar subset is cherry-pickable from worktree impl-4af8-differ-di.","timestamp":1784820377092638001}],"created_at":1783499228219580001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"820da7bb-5172-41a5-9710-0622ed609567","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"44be-2ae1-ba73-46da"},{"link_uuid":"fbb8c3bb-24f2-463c-8be5-e84db2847486","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"44be-2ae1-ba73-46da"},{"link_uuid":"f9abb7a0-4f18-42f7-b032-b5e6a21a6f47","relation":"blocks","target_id":"be74-7832-03a8-48ac"},{"link_uuid":"43c8fcfb-e681-4ae1-b10a-fc7a1d6bbeeb","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"4c1f-7409-6f2d-4010"},{"link_uuid":"a0e4b0ae-76ac-4abc-898a-c4223505f295","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"1b86-3286-bbf9-4a8f"},{"link_uuid":"01fbf838-68d3-4fc9-8b18-dbe2f40d6824","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"24c6-cc8f-04dd-41bb"}],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nPhase 2 of the reconciler vendor-adapter seam (follow-up to 44be / ADR 0035). Phase 1\nauthored ADR 0035, established `adapters/jira/`, and moved `jira_fields.py`. Phase 2 turns\nthe structural seam into an enforced-by-interface one: pin the backend interface (ADR 0035\n§(d), `docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md`), route the core through it, and\ncomplete the physical migration of the remaining Jira modules — so a second backend (GitHub\nIssues, Linear, …) can be added by implementing `adapters/<x>/` with no core rewrite. The\nfirst real second backend is out of scope, tracked by epic `be74-7832-03a8-48ac` (this epic\n`blocks` it).\n\n## Design resolution (the canonical-comparison principle)\n\nThe first attempt to finish core neutrality (ticket 97f2's original plan / Gerrit change\n920) extended the Backend port with the outbound differ's vendor-shaped comparison helpers\n(`_diff_fields` etc., parameterized on Jira snapshot dicts). Plan review blocked it,\ncorrectly: ADR 0035 §(d) says the core owns diff/apply and the port only translates, so\nvendor-shaped helpers belong neither on the port nor in core. The resolution, pinned by this\nepic and to be recorded in ADR 0035 §(d):\n\n**Core compares only canonical (local-vocabulary) shapes. Vendor shapes cross core solely as\nopaque payloads, produced by port calls at emission boundaries\n(`OutboundMapper.map_local_to_remote`, link-payload translation) and consumed by port calls\nat ingestion boundaries (`InboundMapper.map_remote_to_local`, remote-link reading).** The\ninbound differ already works this way (`inbound_differ.py:159`); the remaining children\nbring the outbound differ, link differ, absence probe, and rich-text/comment-limit paths to\nparity, plus the scalar port surface (project scope, env-readiness, neutral exceptions).\nGerrit change 920 is abandoned; its scalar subset is salvageable by cherry-pick from\nworktree `impl-4af8-differ-di` (see re-scoped child 97f2).\n\n## Child decomposition\n\nLanded and closed:\n\n- S1 `ef33-eaf6-a545-4bfb` — ADR 0035 §(d) pins the interface (change 900).\n- S2 `ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798` — Backend port + role/capability Protocols + `RemoteRef` + thin\n  `JiraBackend` + contract suite (901).\n- S3 `94f9-a9a0-7475-4e75` — `reconciler.backend` config + in-tree registry +\n  `select_backend()` (902).\n- S4 `6673-7636-a116-4f90` — 4 transport-construction sites routed through\n  `select_backend().transport`; provider literals → `backend.vendor`; ~34 test doubles\n  migrated (903).\n- S5 `dfb9-d2d1-455d-48d9` — 8 vendor modules physically relocated into `adapters/jira/`\n  (acli*, adf, outbound_fields, comment_limits) + loader/import updates (905).\n- `4af8-2d88-719e-4478` — vendor mapper entrypoints injected into\n  outbound_differ/inbound_differ/apply_inbound via the port (914).\n\nOpen (the remaining neutrality work, disjoint edit-sets, independently reviewable,\nparallel-safe):\n\n- `97f2-2d98-2eff-41c1` (re-scoped) — scalar port surface: `project`/`query_project`,\n  `assert_env_ready()`, neutral `BackendAssigneeNotFoundError`; rewires fetcher, applier,\n  apply_handlers, _attestation.\n- Canonical-shape outbound field diff — the differ canonicalizes the snapshot via\n  `InboundMapper` and diffs local-vs-local; vendor payload built only via the injected\n  `OutboundMapper` at emission; vendor comparison helpers become adapter-internal; ADR §(d)\n  amendment.\n- Canonical link diff — `SupportsLinks` gains `map_remote_links` +\n  `link_payload_for_relation`; `outbound_links.py` compares canonical relations only.\n- Vendor absence probe behind `SupportsAbsenceProbe` — Jira REST probe mechanics move to\n  `adapters/jira/probe.py`; neutral `ProbeBranch`/`ProbeResult` vocabulary stays in core.\n- Canonicalize `reconcile_check.py` (`ad44-9f46-07aa-480c`, depends_on the canonical field\n  diff) — the checker's local-vs-snapshot comparison reuses the canonical differ machinery\n  (`InboundMapper` canonicalization, `assignee_identity` membership, sanitizer description\n  parity); its by-path loads of `adapters/jira/outbound_fields.py`/`adf.py` are deleted and\n  the gate's documented reconcile_check carve-out is removed.\n- Rich-text codec + comment limits behind the port — `outbound_comments.py` and\n  `inbound_translate.py` route through `FieldSanitizer`/`InboundMapper`; the\n  `\"rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira\"` lazy-key literals are deleted; a sweep gate bans the\n  literal in package-root core (single recorded exemption: `inbound_fields.py`, the Jira\n  InboundMapper implementation pending physical relocation — tracked by follow-up ticket\n  `556a-5a1f-adb3-4139`, linked `discovered_from` this epic, out of scope here).\n\n## Success Criteria\n\nA second backend can be introduced by implementing `adapters/<x>/` against the Backend port\nalone: no package-root core module names, imports, lazy-loads, or shape-compares anything\nJira-specific. Every deliverable above is covered by exactly one child; children do not\noverlap (each owns disjoint core modules; shared `_backend.py`/`adapters/jira/backend.py`\nedits are additive per child and recorded in each child's file impact).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] ADR 0035 §(d) pins the interface (S1); Backend Protocols, `RemoteRef`, contract suite\n      passing both `JiraBackend` and test-only `FakeBackend` exist (S2) — landed, changes\n      900/901.\n- [ ] Backend chosen via `config.reconciler.backend` through the registry; default `\"jira\"`\n      reproduces prior behavior end-to-end (S3) — landed, change 902.\n- [ ] All transport construction and provider literals route through the port (S4); the 8\n      vendor modules physically reside under `adapters/jira/` with loaders repointed and no\n      re-export shims (S5) — landed, changes 903/905.\n- [ ] **Zero vendor reach-through in core:** every package-root\n      `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/*.py` module has NO `adapters.jira`/\n      `acli_subprocess` import (module-level or function-nested), NO\n      `\"rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira\"` lazy-key literal, and NO by-path load of a vendor\n      sibling (an `adapters/jira/...` path literal, the `reconcile_check.py:61-75` pattern)\n      — single recorded exemption: `inbound_fields.py`, the Jira InboundMapper\n      implementation — verified by the union of AST/sweep cases in\n      `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py` added by the open children\n      (incl. the removal of that gate's documented reconcile_check carve-out), green on\n      main.\n- [ ] **Canonical comparison:** the outbound field and link differs compare only canonical\n      shapes; vendor payloads are built/consumed exclusively via port calls; ADR 0035 §(d)\n      records the principle — verified by the canonical-diff children's characterization and\n      neutrality tests, green on main.\n- [ ] All `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/*.py` modules respect the 800-LOC module-size\n      gate (`.github/module-size-limit.txt`); the full suite is behavior-preserving (all\n      children's `make lint && make typecheck && make test` green; each landed with\n      LLM-Review +1 and Verified +1).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["blocks","be74-7832-03a8-48ac"],["relates_to","1b86-3286-bbf9-4a8f"],["relates_to","24c6-cc8f-04dd-41bb"],["relates_to","44be-2ae1-ba73-46da"],["relates_to","4c1f-7409-6f2d-4010"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"c3b73802-08e4-4c05-94de-16630de1ba0b","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","ticket_type":"epic","title":"Reconciler vendor-adapter seam Phase 2: pin backend interface, route core through it, relocate Jira modules into adapters/jira/","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["421f11c4-8c98-41ba-b9b4-09cc0108778d","820da7bb-5172-41a5-9710-0622ed609567","fbb8c3bb-24f2-463c-8be5-e84db2847486","4241dc1f-384d-47ed-8d15-7df9ff4d3316","f9abb7a0-4f18-42f7-b032-b5e6a21a6f47","6581eabc-0dd7-4690-a8d4-3b21624fdbd2","87baf244-fa9d-4a84-8312-0331f5120719","85f8318e-b40b-41ad-bcfb-960fbbc16515","7876661e-b5ed-4c95-9508-e8b13f4f0c1d","42e58d29-05c3-4023-a921-8e2929e0cde3","3de44b71-b6c1-4e35-a8e8-e1dfd07373cb","e96298af-6214-45ac-b633-367a067fec03","914ea492-0207-43df-8183-67f855f068f0","2f2c3a81-c72a-45b8-be2f-3f1dc5b68596","43c8fcfb-e681-4ae1-b10a-fc7a1d6bbeeb","a098f918-1b0f-4961-bc14-53521d7b4cde","c3b73802-08e4-4c05-94de-16630de1ba0b","df2dda15-1450-4889-90bd-038727e95050","1f6b57a0-b02e-41ee-9cc7-910993250f28","d47b4a5a-13dc-4876-88f1-8e21db23dcf0","665a3991-e130-4ffc-9051-96ba5f8e1e4e","d6e51027-6fd9-41b6-98bc-4e19c3d00a08","29bd173f-bbe6-4dd5-b743-adc885ec3510","a0e4b0ae-76ac-4abc-898a-c4223505f295","01fbf838-68d3-4fc9-8b18-dbe2f40d6824","efb2b4c9-d1fa-4600-a8b3-63a242d9264c","1138b92e-2788-4faa-8470-0e67c9e7ed08"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784827909348291976,"uuid":"696d42ff-b48e-4f8d-97d9-5c2501c43c09"}